job_summary:
This role is part of the Global Digital & Technology (D&T) department of HEINEKEN International. D&T is proud to bring cutting-edge innovation, strong technology, and advanced analytics to HEINEKEN. With speed and agility, we ensure HEINEKEN has the technological competitive advantages it needs to deliver on its ambition.


Your role at HEINEKEN


The Toolkit Security Specialist is part of the Toolkit portfolio and supports multiple Product teams within it (e.g. Toolchain, Digital integration, Robotics & Automation, Digital Enablement) and is one of the professionals who do the work of delivering a potentially releasable increment of the product at the end of each sprint. Product Teams are structured and empowered by the organization to self-organize and manage their own work. The resulting synergy optimizes the Product Team’s overall efficiency and effectiveness.


The strategy for all Toolkit products is to continue to evolve the technology platforms in their scope and to actively grow adoption of the platform. To a large extend this will be done by means of a federated operating model, allowing other regional/local teams to develop on the platforms. To avoid this is introducing security risks special focus from the security specialist is required.


You will be working alongside with a colleague in HEINEKEN’s Global Shared Services Hub where the emphasis of this job role is on the functional and organisational side, while that emphasis is on the technical side for your HGSS colleague.


In this role, you will:

The Security technical specialist will assist with the design, development, and implementation of security measures for solutions deployed into various cloud, hybrid, and on-premises systems in HEINEKEN environment. 
Ensure security by design principles are upheld in the implemented products.
Overseeing that Toolkit portfolio team members understand and properly use the Solution Security Procedures.
Ensure embedding of joint security responsibility models definition related to federated governance systems.
Thoroughly document security decisions and implementations. 
Provide input and feedback on security architectures/setup/configuration.
Perform risk assessments on any new resource/application/functionality implemented in the cloud platforms.
Participate in the Security and Quality Assurance chapter and help embed security by design mindset into the HEINEKEN organization.
Ensure performance and automation of compliance and security controls.
Support product teams in security decisions related to the product platforms, by helping team members and training them so that they can do more of this themselves.
Support in automating continuous security testing for the product platforms.
Support in resolving any security related audit or compliancy issues.



Are we looking for you?


As qualifications, our ideal candidate would have:



2-4 years working experience in security operations and advanced level of understanding regarding systems security at both technical and procedural level;
2-4 years’ experience with Security Architect and/or Engineering;


Operational experience in securing one or more of the following solutions; 

low /no code platforms (e.g. OutSystems)
Robotics process automation (e.g. UiPath) 
Integration and middleware platforms (Boomi, API Connect, SAP PO) 
SLDC Tools (e.g. Azure DevOps, Confluence, Zephyr, SonarQube)
Microsoft Power platforms



Possess a solid understanding and have experience with systems automation platforms and technologies;
Certifications such as CEH, CIR, CISM, CISA, CGEDIT, any of the OWASP or similar are a plus;
Knowledge of industry standard security frameworks for information systems (NIST, ISO 27001/2, CSA, COBIT), the Cyber Kill Chain & MITRE ATT&CK framework;
Being able to translate technical language into a story that can be understood, and cohesively present it back to different stakeholders with a clear message;
Bachelor’s degree or equivalent experience;
Have a passion for security and enjoys solving problems;
You understand the Agile mindset and have basic knowledge on working in a Scrum Team. You show end-to-end ownership on work that you do;
Excellent knowledge of English, written and verbal;
You have experience with outsourced managed services;
You look for structural solutions over one-time quick fixes;
Experience representing technical viewpoints to diverse audiences and in making timely and prudent technical risk decisions.



What is in it for you?


At HEINEKEN, we have a proud reputation for the many career opportunities we offer our employees. Your career has the opportunity for being a unique journey, with a steep learning curve, across various brands, businesses or geographies. Next to a collaborative, international working environment, we will offer you a very rewarding salary and excellent secondary benefits.


This includes:

An extensive and rewarding pension-plan;
Various training courses as part of your personal development plan;
Employee discount for health insurances;
Remuneration for travel expenses;
Flexible working hours and the flexibility for working from home.



We are HEINEKEN


Our proud history as a family-owned, independent brewer stretches back 150 years. We brew the highest quality beers, build globally loved brands and strive to do both of these things as sustainably as possible.
With a larger global presence than any other brewer in the business, we’re able to draw strength from the diverse regions we operate in and sell to – driving consumer trends and opening up new market opportunities in the process.


No matter where our more than 84,000 global employees are based or what role they play, each one is driven by the same goals and united under the same values.


Embracing and celebrating diversity is core to HEINEKEN’s purpose of “brewing the joy of true togetherness to inspire a better world”. We believe that people as diverse as our brews – including and not limited to gender, ethnicity, age, sexual orientation, religious belief, nationality, social background, disability and thinking style – enrich our lives and strengthen our business. We welcome and consider applications from all qualified candidates as we champion a culture of belonging that provides fair and equal opportunities for all.


It’s what makes us proud to say We Are HEINEKEN.

About the role 
You may not have heard of us, but you’ll know our brands! A.S. Watson is the world's largest international health and beauty retailer with over 17,000 stores in 27 markets. Each year, over 5.9 billion customers and members shop with our well-known retail brands, both online and offline, including the likes of Superdrug, Kruidvat, Watson’s, Marionnaud, The Perfume Shop, and many more. 

 In this role, you will be supporting with protecting the largest health and beauty retailer from cyber threats by establishing a strong foundation around infrastructure security topics. Cyber security should not slow the business down but become a property and ability of our business units. You will become part of the infrastructure team, be able to communicate effectively with IT and business stakeholders, and make effective use of the available security tools and processes to ensure we are cyber ready. 

 You will be able to proactively identify, reduce and eliminate the risks to our infrastructure operations. Linking in with a range of stakeholders you will help to define the cyber security related to infrastructure and ensure buy-in and active support. 

 The overall purpose of the job is to develop, update, refine and maintain our infrastructure security framework at Group level as well influencing the same at our business unit level. 

 As a Infrastructure Security Engineer, you are responsible for: 
Vulnerability Management; 
AV & EDR solutions; 
NDR solutions; 
SIEM Infrastructure; 
Privileged Access and Identity Management; 
Azure and Office365 Security elements and services; 
Network Assurance program. 
What will you get in return? 
A job at a successful international company that is constantly evolving. You'll never be bored! 
You will be based at our office in Renswoude, Heteren or Utrecht; 
Competitive salary and benefits like travel allowance and a discount in your health insurance; 
30 days holiday with an option to buy more; 
Excellent refer-a-friend scheme with up to €1.000,00 up for grabs! 
A fantastic learning and development offering to explore; 
Discounts for you and your family from some our much-loved retailers in the Netherlands, including Kruidvat, Trekpleister and ICI Paris XL; 
Lots of opportunities to get involved in wellbeing initiatives to support your physical and mental health; 
…plus much More! 

 This is you 


This role would be a good fit for you if:
 You enjoy being technically stretched; 
Making a significant difference to the business gives you a buzz; 
You understand the importance of communication; 
You enjoy complex problem solving; 
You can adapt swiftly to change; 
You enjoy a multicultural environment; 
Business travel is not a turn-off; 
Multi-tasking comes easily to you; 
You have a very inquisitive mind backed by logical thinking. 


What you'll need:
 A deep understanding of business risk; 
Practical experience of handling security incidents; 
Working experience of the core security principles; 
A strong foundation in core IT services and process; 
Experience in deploying new technologies and process’s; 
An understanding and empathy when working with different cultures; 
The ability to communicate complex models in a simple fashion; 
At least 5 years of IT experience; 
Good Dutch and English communication skills both verbal and written; 
It would be preferable if you have a recognized security certification. 
We invite you to apply for this job via the apply button (‘solliciteer online’). By clicking on this button, you will be forwarded to this vacancy on our A.S. Watson Group Careerpage, where you are able to learn More about A.S. Watson Group.

Do you want to make an impact, are you tech savvy, digital driven, analytically strong and curious? And, do you feel genuinely interested in cyber security? Then you are the ideal candidate!

 Requirements


 You have 0-3 years of work experience;
 You have completed a higher professional or university programme (BA or MA) in IT (as your main subject or area of specialisation, e.g. Software Engineering, Information Science, Information Technology, Cyber security);
 You speak fluent English and preferably also fluent Dutch, this may be a requirement for some teams;
 You are a team player;
 You are genuinely interested in cyber Security, forensic IT, privacy and/or Identity & access management.


 What do we offer?


 A challenging and fulfilling work environment;
 Multiple training possibilities that contribute to your personal development;
 A Suitable salary and extensive labor conditions such as a ‘well-being-budget’. This is a personal budget of €750,- which you may spend on your own health such as: Mindfulness, sports, lifestyle coaching, wellness but also technical gadgets such as a second screen for your home office;
 A monthly reimbursement for your internet at home;
 A lease car or car allowance;
 A laptop or Mac and Iphone.


 Apply now!

 Are you interested in this vacancy and do you meet the requirements? Have a look at our application process or apply directly by clicking the button. We would like to receive the following documents:

 Resume
 Cover letter

 At PwC Diversity and Inclusion are on top of mind.
 If you have specific questions about this vacancy you can email to Brigitte Bekenkamp, Talent Acquisition CF&P, brigitte.bekenkamp@pwc.com.

Ben je klaar voor een echte uitdaging en ga jij ervoor zorgen dat de data van onze klanten goed beveiligd is? Als Security Engineer los je graag complexe issues op, ben je enthousiast over cyber security en wil je jezelf graag verder ontwikkelen.

 Wat ga je doen?
 Als Security Engineer werk je in het SOC (Security Operations Center) en op een ultra moderne werkplek. Je dagen zijn dynamisch en wisselen zich af in het oplossen van complexe netwerk problemen tot het volledig segmenteren van het netwerk van de klant. Altijd met een focus op security en je mag al je energie en expertise gebruiken in dit proces. Door jouw kennis van IT en infrastructuur lukt het jou om, ongeacht het product, het probleem aan te pakken. Je verantwoordelijkheden bestaan onder andere uit:

 Het oplossen van security problemen in routering en netwerken;
 Werken met protocollen zoals SSH, SSL, HTTPS, SMTP en DHCP;
 Deelnemen aan projecten en samenwerken met collega’s van andere afdelingen;
 Het analyseren van afwijkingen en potentiële bedreigingen;
 Het adviseren van klanten en collega’s.


 Wie zijn wij?
 Wij zijn een internationaal bedrijf met een Nederlandse oorsprong. Met ongeveer 90 werknemers hebben wij de ambitie om met onze innovatieve diensten een wereldspeler in managed cybersecurity te worden. De stap naar de VS hebben we al gezet. Met onze ambities willen we voorop blijven lopen in het beveiligen van onze digitale samenleving en manier van leven. We hebben een informele en open cultuur en je werkt met collega’s die elkaar elke dag inspireren. Samen bouwen we aan een nog mooiere toekomst. Wij hebben een grote focus op onze internationale groei en klantverwachtingen willen wij overstijgen.

 Wie ben jij?
 Je bent ontzettend enthousiast over IT en technologie en hebt een grote affiniteit met cyber security. Jij houdt van een uitdaging en je vind het geen probleem om buiten je comfort zone te treden. Je kan niet wachten om jezelf te ontwikkelen met (senior) collega’s die jou assisteren in jouw groeipad. Je bent bereid om trainingen te volgen en je bent geïnteresseerd in datalekken en analyses. Verder neem jij mee naar ON2IT:

 Afgeronde studie in de richting van Informatie Technologie of Cyber Security;
 Bekendheid met VPN en DMZ;
 Kennis van veelgebruikte systemen zoals Windows, Mac en Linux;
 Kennis van netwerken: routers, switches en firewalls (CCNA);
 Goede communicatieve vaardigheden;
 Uitstekende beheersing van de Nederlandse taal en werk-niveau Engels.


 Wat bieden wij jou?
 Wij bieden jou mogelijkheden om jezelf te ontwikkelen door het volgen van trainingen en opleidingen. Jouw senior collega’s staan ook altijd voor je klaar om jou te inspireren en jou te begeleiden in je leerproces. Op kantoor staat iedere middag een uitgebreide en goed verzorgde lunch voor je klaar en we hebben heerlijke koffie.

 Hoe ziet onze procedure eruit?
 Hebben wij jou weten te enthousiasmeren? We zien jouw sollicitatie graag tegemoet. Je kunt solliciteren door op onderstaande knop te drukken.
 Heb je geen up to date CV of heb je vragen over de procedure? Bel of stuur een WhatsApp naar Tamara Burgerhof, Corporate Recruiter via +31 (0)6 1004 9295 om de mogelijkheden te bespreken.

Vind jij ook dat collega’s samen een belangrijke rol spelen bij een organisatie? Bij dit bedrijf geloven ze erin dat een diverse organisatie de ideale voedingsbron is voor creativiteit, samenwerking en innovatie. Sta jij open voor een nieuwe uitdaging waarin je zowel administratief aan de slag gaat als aan de knoppen kunt draaien? Lees dan deze vacature!
 Organisatie
 Deze organisatie is opgericht in 1989 en onderdeel van een grote holding. Met een groot aantal Internationale vestigingen zijn ze opgericht vanuit het ideaal structureel geld te genereren voor goede doelenorganisaties die een bijdrage leveren aan een betere en leefbare wereld. Met een mooi kantoor in Amsterdam waar iedereen met veel plezier naartoe gaat staat een prettige werksfeer centraal.
 Functie
 Voor de afdeling Risk Managent & Legal is deze organisatie op zoek naar een Junior Security Officer. Regelgeving, compliance, internal audit, privacy en security zijn de werkterreinen van de afdeling Risk Management & Legal. Juist door de diversiteit aan functies en medewerkers zorgt dit voor een dynamische afdeling die, ondanks haar relatief beperkt grootte, van wezenlijk belang is. Zij werken hiervoor samen met collega’s in binnen- en buitenland. In deze functie ga je verschillende activiteiten op het gebied van Cyber Security en Security-awareness opzetten. Denk hierbij aan:

Opzetten en begeleiden van onze security awareness campagnes;
Interne communicatie namens de Security Office;
Beoordelen van beveiligingsaspecten bij onze leveranciers;
Coördineren van pentesten door externe partijen;
Organiseren Security trainingen;
Ondersteunen bij het opstellen van informatiebeveiligingsbeleid;
Ondersteunen van de ISO27001 Audit;
Samenwerken met onze internationale loterijen (voertaal Engels).

Eisen

Bij voorkeur in het bezit van een hbo/wo diploma;
Minimaal één jaar ervaring op het gebied van informatiebeveiliging;
Je hebt kennis van
Je bent procesmatig sterk, stelt je flexibel op en beheerst de Engelse taal;

Arbeidsvoorwaarden

Een maximaal salaris van €50.000-, per jaar;
Een werkweek van 32-40 uur;
25 Vakantiedagen;
Flexibiliteit in werktijden en werkplek;
opleidingsmogelijkheden en optie tot behalen van certificaten.

